
[1]conclusion

   CONCLUSION, n. [L.]

   1. End; close; the last part; as the conclusion of an address.

   2. The close of an argument, debate or reasoning; inference that ends
   the discussion; final result.

   Let us hear the conclusion of the whole matter; fear God, and keep his
   commandments; for this is the whole of man. Ecclesiastes 12.

   3. Determination; final decision.

   After long debate, the house of commons came to this conclusion.

   4. Consequence; inference; that which is collected or drawn from
   premises; particular deduction from propositions, facts, experience, or
   reasoning.

   5. The event of experiments; experiment.

   We practice all conclusions of grafting and inoculating. [Little used.]

   6. Confinement of the thoughts; silence. [Not used.]
